
Overview of noun phantom

The noun phantom has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) apparition, phantom, phantasm, phantasma, fantasm, specter, spectre -- (a ghostly appearing figure; "we were unprepared for the apparition that confronted us")
2. (1) apparition, phantom, phantasm, phantasma, fantasm, shadow -- (something existing in perception only; "a ghostly apparition at midnight")

Overview of adj phantom

The adj phantom has 1 sense (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
